<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOVIMA; REGAL MODEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dovima, 63, sophisticated, regal model of the 1950s. Born Dorothy Virginia 
Margaret Juba in Jackson Heights, N.Y., she constructed her professional name 
from the first two letters of her three given names. 
</P>
<P>
In 1955, photographer Richard Avedon posed her in a sashed black evening gown 
between two elephants. The picture in Harper's Bazaar became one of the most 
widely anthologized of all fashion photographs. In Ft. Lauderdale, Fla., on 
Thursday of liver cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
