<HEADLINE>
<P>
MASON E. HALE; BOTANIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mason E. Hale, 61, Smithsonian Institution botanist and international expert on 
lichens. Author of 150 scholarly articles and five books on lichens, he studied 
lichens as indicators of pollution for the U.S. Forest Service in the mountains 
of West Virginia, Colorado and Wyoming. In Arlington, Va., on April 30 of 
cancer. 
</P>
