<TEXT>
<P>
Rejecting a management offer by an 86% majority, nearly 1,000 Kaiser Permanente 
registered nurses at facilities on Sunset Boulevard in Los Angeles and in 
Inglewood voted to go on strike next Sunday at 12:01 a.m., union officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The walkout would follow a 10-day strike by other employees of Kaiser in Los 
Angeles and Orange counties last month. The nurses voted Monday on the offer by 
the health maintenance organization. 
