<HEADLINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON IRVING BRANCH LIBRARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to your April 27 editorial, "The Little Library That Could": 
</P>
<P>
Do we need an expensive community center? No. Do we need a larger, full-service 
library? Yes. 
</P>
<P>
The option of expanding the current Washington Irving branch library was 
somehow overlooked by your staff. A large number in our community have voiced 
their desire to retain the current library facility and expand it to meet the 
required service standards. Expansion is the only clear solution. 
</P>
<P>
There has been no convincing argument made in support of relocation. If there 
is a compelling argument to be made for relocation, make it. But next time, 
make it before you advocate the misuse of public monies or the abandonment of a 
64-year-old library. 
</P>
<P>
PAUL PRATT 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
