<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFFSHORE DRILLING CONTROVERSY AND MEETING PETROLEUM NEEDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ask a class for the definition of the word cowardice, and I supply the answer: 
The Times' editorial board. 
</P>
<P>
The April 27 editorial asks "Want to Be Held Hostage Again?" But in the 
cowardly reply, you say not a single word about either increased domestic 
production or more nuclear power. Either or both of these will most certainly 
reduce our scary future, but you are afraid to mention either for fear of 
offending certain people. 
</P>
<P>
Shame. How can you claim to speak for all the people when you permit the 
calamity howlers (and I do mean howl) to deter you from speaking honestly? 
</P>
<P>
Is it that tough to be honest? 
</P>
<P>
EDWARD H. MOSS 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 
</P>
