<P>
CAL POLY POMONA NEARS NCAA TENNIS TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RANCHO CORDOVA, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal Poly Pomona won seven tiebreakers and moved to within one victory of its 
first national title with a 5-2 semifinal win over fourth-ranked Abilene 
Christian at the NCAA Division II Women's Tennis Championships Monday. 
</P>
<P>
In today's final, the top-ranked Broncos (24-1) play UC Davis, which beat Cal 
Poly San Luis Obispo, 5-4. 
</P>
<P>
"This is a group of athletes that play great as a team," Bronco Coach Ann 
Lebedeff said. "They are very competitive." 
</P>
<P>
That competitive edge was apparent after All-American Onnaca Heron (21-7) lost 
to Abilene Christian's Michelle King in the No. 1 singles, as Pomona won four 
of the next five matches. 
</P>
