<P>
T-Bill Rates Fall: The Treasury sold $8.4 billion of news three-month bills at 
an average discount rate of 7.79%, down from 7.91% last week. 
</P>
<P>
Another $8.4 billion of new six-month bills was sold at an average discount 
rate of 7.84%, down from 8.03% last week. The new discount rates understate the 
actual return to investors -- 8.06% for three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill 
selling for $9,803.10, and 8.29% for a six-month bill selling for $9,603.60. 
The discount rate reflects the price discount received when government 
securities are purchased at less than face value. 
</P>
