<HEADLINE>
<P>
300 FLEE FLOODING IN ARKANSAS AREAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Floodwaters surged down the Arkansas River on Monday, forcing more than 300 
people to flee their homes and causing millions of dollars in damage to roads, 
bridges and buildings in what may be the worst flooding in Arkansas in 63 
years. 
</P>
<P>
Some 327 homes have been evacuated in six Arkansas counties along the Arkansas 
River. 
</P>
<P>
Emergency workers said 182 homes were evacuated in Jefferson County and 
predicted an additional 200 evacuations before the flooding ends. The river is 
expected to crest today in Little Rock and Wednesday in Pine Bluff, Jefferson 
County, about 40 miles downstream. 
</P>
<P>
A Pulaski County judge on Monday called in the National Guard and declared a 
state of emergency in the county to prevent further looting in some evacuated 
neighborhoods northwest of Little Rock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
