<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO SEX TILL IT'S OVER, COACH ASKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COVERCIANO, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The coach of Italy's national soccer team has asked his players not to engage 
in sex until the World Cup tournament ends July 8. 
</P>
<P>
Azeglio Vicini said Monday that this weekend will be the last at liberty for 
the players before a long period of "seclusion." 
</P>
<P>
"Chastity of players prior and during a major competition has been a 
long-debated but unsolved problem," Vicini said. 
</P>
<P>
For entertainment, he said, the players will have videotapes and a few 
excursions out of the training center -- under the watchful eye of Vicini and 
other team officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Sidebar; Wire 
</P>
