<P>
The Australian Open, long considered the least prestigious of tennis' four 
major titles, could lose its Grand Slam status unless prize money is sharply 
increased, the tournament's general manager said. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Reid said the tournament was having a hard time matching the purses offered 
by the three other Grand Slam events -- Wimbledon, the French Open and the U.S. 
Open. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, Wimbledon offered $5.2 million, followed by the U.S. Open with $5.1 
million, the French Open with $4.5 million and the Australian Open with $3 
million. 
</P>
<P>
