<HEADLINE>
<P>
STRAY SHOT BY POLICE KILLS WOMAN AT BUS STOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BRUSSELS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman waiting for a bus was killed Monday and a man was wounded when police 
opened fire to stop a truck from barreling into a group of demonstrators, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Neither victim was involved in the demonstration by about 500 workers 
protesting the possible closing of their company, a gunpowder factory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
