ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TODAY'S ELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What: Voters in Seal Beach go to the polls today to fill two seats on the City 
Council. This is a runoff election between the top vote-getters in the March 27 
election. 
</P>
<P>
Who: There are four candidates running for the two seats. 
</P>
<P>
In District 1, the candidates are: Marilyn Bruce Hastings, 61, a property 
management specialist, and Joe Rullo, 54, an engineering contractor. 
</P>
<P>
In District 2, the candidates are Galen F. Ambrose, 49, a financial controller, 
and Gwen Forsythe, 35, a financial manager for an advertising agency. 
</P>
<P>
Where: District 1 polling places are at Marina Community Center, McGaugh School 
gym and Clubhouse 1 in Leisure World. 
</P>
<P>
District 2 polling places are at Fire Station 44, St. Anne's Church Hall and 
Surfside Colony office. 
</P>
<P>
When: Polls are open from 7 a.m. to 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Information: For more information, call the Seal Beach City Clerk's office at 
(213) 431-2527. 
</P>
