<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCI SELLS MORE SERVICE TO AMERICAN EXPRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MCI Communications Corp. said it was awarded a non-exclusive three-year 
contract by American Express Co. to provide data, messaging and voice-network 
services. 
</P>
<P>
The contract is the largest awarded MCI by American Express since the two 
companies began working together in the early 1970s. It includes an option for 
an additional two-year period, making a potential five-year arrangement valued 
at up to $100 million, according to MCI President Bert C. Roberts Jr. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for MCI to provide services to all five American Express 
operating units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
