<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
BUSH VOWS BOLIVIA AID INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush today assured Bolivian President Jaime Paz Zamora that "you and 
your countrymen will not stand alone" in fighting cocaine and trying to improve 
Bolivia's ailing economy. 
</P>
<P>
Winding up three hours of talks at the White House, Bush promised that he would 
seek a substantial increase in economic aid for Bolivia next year, beyond the 
$88 million earmarked for this year. He said Paz, in their private talks, had 
stressed the importance of Bolivia's receiving development assistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
