<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
DENIS, 74, PASSES HIS PRIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Denis Thatcher arrived back at 10 Downing Street today from a visit to the 
United States and failed to notice his wife waiting in the front hall. 
</P>
<P>
"Hello, how are you," cried Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher as her husband, 
who turns 75 Thursday, headed for their private apartment on the top floor of 
10 Downing Street. 
</P>
<P>
Stopped in his tracks, Denis turned, gave her a quick kiss and strode off. 
</P>
<P>
His wife, waiting to meet Vice President Dan Quayle, called after him: "I am 
waiting for the vice president. Would you like to meet him?" 
</P>
<P>
"I need a shave," Denis called over his shoulder as he disappeared upstairs. 
</P>
<P>
A smiling prime minister told reporters and photographers: "He's just back from 
America. He wasn't expecting a reception committee." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Denis Thatcher 
</P>
