<P>
P. M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
EL AL TELLS $24.2-MILLION PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State-owned El Al Israel Airlines today reported profit of $24.2 million for 
1989, its fourth consecutive year in the black. 
</P>
<P>
The profit marked a 28.7% jump from El Al's 1988 earnings of $18.8 million. 
Revenues rose 7.2% to $713.6 million from $665.3 million in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
El Al said it carried 1.74 million passengers last year, 12% more than in 1988, 
when tourism to Israel fell sharply in the early months of a Palestinian 
uprising in Israeli-annexed East Jerusalem and the occupied West Bank and Gaza 
Strip. 
</P>
<P>
The sustained profitability is likely to enhance prospects of floating El Al 
shares on the Tel Aviv and foreign stock exchanges, proposed as part of 
Israel's privatization drive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
